The most secure and user-friendly messengers protect your messages with strong encryption, making it very hard for outsiders to read your chats. However, even the best encryption can’t stop threats like trojans—malicious software that can secretly spy on your device, capturing messages before they’re encrypted or after they’re decrypted. This means protecting your device itself is just as important as using a secure messenger. To stay safe, combine encrypted messaging with good device security and avoid downloading suspicious files. Keywords: “encrypted messenger,” “trojan malware,” “device security.”